---
import PipeBlock from "../PipeBlock.astro";
---

<section class="install wrap">
  <h2>Get the binary.</h2>
  <PipeBlock
    caption="One line."
    code={'npm install -g luna-agents'}
    output={['installed: luna-agents@latest', 'verify:  luna --version']}
  />
  <p>
    Luna Agents ships as a <strong>CLI</strong> and a <strong>Claude Code plugin</strong>.
    Both expose the same lexicon. Pipes work in your terminal, your editor,
    and your CI. See <a href="/install">Chapter 04</a> for platform-specific notes.
  </p>
</section>

<style>
  .install { padding-top: var(--t-8); padding-bottom: var(--t-12); }
</style>
